        <span class="roadmap-tab-label">Data Science</span>
      </button>
      <button class="roadmap-tab" role="tab" type="button" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="panel-mobile" id="tab-mobile" data-tab="mobile">
        <span class="roadmap-tab-icon" aria-hidden="true">📱</span>
        <span class="roadmap-tab-label">Mobile</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <!-- ============================== -->
    <!-- FRONTEND PANEL -->
    <!-- ============================== -->
    <div class="roadmap-panel roadmap-panel-active" role="tabpanel" id="panel-frontend" aria-labelledby="tab-frontend">

      <div class="roadmap-intro">
        <h3>Frontend Developer</h3>
        <p class="roadmap-intro-desc">Build the visual interfaces users interact with. Translate designs into responsive, accessible web experiences using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and modern frameworks.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- ROLE OVERVIEW -->
      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Role Overview &amp; Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>Frontend developers create everything users see and interact with in web applications. You implement designs from mockups, ensure responsive layouts work across devices, optimize performance, handle user interactions, integrate with backend APIs, and maintain accessibility standards. The role requires both technical skill and design sensitivity.</p>
        <p>Daily work involves writing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, debugging cross-browser issues, optimizing load times, implementing new features, reviewing code, and collaborating with designers and backend developers. You'll spend significant time in the browser DevTools testing and debugging.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- SKILLS PROGRESSION -->
      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Required Skills: Beginner → Advanced</h3>
        <div class="skills-progression">
          <div class="skill-level">
            <div class="skill-level-header">
              <span class="skill-level-badge skill-level-beginner">Beginner</span>
              <span class="skill-level-time">0–6 months</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="skill-level-list">
              <li>HTML5 semantic elements</li>
              <li>CSS fundamentals (box model, flexbox, grid)</li>
              <li>JavaScript basics (variables, functions, DOM)</li>
              <li>Responsive design principles</li>
              <li>Git version control basics</li>
              <li>Browser DevTools</li>
              <li>Basic accessibility (WCAG guidelines)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="skill-level">
            <div class="skill-level-header">
              <span class="skill-level-badge skill-level-intermediate">Intermediate</span>
              <span class="skill-level-time">6–18 months</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="skill-level-list">
              <li>React, Vue, or Angular framework</li>
              <li>JavaScript ES6+ features</li>
