      <div class="roadmap-intro">
        <h3>Backend Developer</h3>
        <p class="roadmap-intro-desc">Build the server-side logic, databases, and APIs that power applications. Handle data processing, business logic, security, and system architecture behind the scenes.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Role Overview &amp; Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>Backend developers create the server-side components that applications depend on. You design and implement APIs, manage databases, handle authentication and authorization, process business logic, integrate third-party services, and ensure systems scale reliably. The role focuses on data integrity, performance, and security.</p>
        <p>Daily work includes writing server code in Python, Java, Node.js, or similar languages, designing database schemas, optimizing SQL queries, debugging production issues, reviewing code, writing tests, and monitoring system performance. You'll work closely with frontend developers to define API contracts and with DevOps on deployment strategies.</p>
      </div>

