      <div class="roadmap-intro">
        <h3>Full Stack Developer</h3>
        <p class="roadmap-intro-desc">Master both frontend and backend development. Build complete features from database to user interface, handling every layer of the application stack.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Role Overview &amp; Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>Full stack developers handle end-to-end feature development. You implement UI components, write server logic, design databases, integrate APIs, and deploy applications. The role requires breadth of knowledge across the entire technology stack, making you versatile and valuable in smaller teams or startups where wearing multiple hats is necessary.</p>
        <p>Daily work involves context switching between frontend React components and backend API endpoints, troubleshooting issues across the stack, making architectural decisions, and understanding how different layers interact. You need strong fundamentals in both domains without necessarily being an expert in every technology.</p>
      </div>

