    <div class="roadmap-panel" role="tabpanel" id="panel-devops" aria-labelledby="tab-devops" hidden>

      <div class="roadmap-intro">
        <h3>DevOps Engineer</h3>
        <p class="roadmap-intro-desc">Bridge development and operations. Automate deployments, manage infrastructure, ensure reliability, and optimize the software delivery pipeline for speed and stability.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Role Overview &amp; Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>DevOps engineers focus on automation, infrastructure, and reliability. You build CI/CD pipelines, manage cloud resources, containerize applications, monitor system health, respond to incidents, and optimize deployment processes. The role requires deep understanding of both software development and systems administration, enabling teams to ship code faster and more reliably.</p>
        <p>Daily work includes writing infrastructure as code, debugging deployment failures, optimizing build times, configuring monitoring and alerting, managing Kubernetes clusters, responding to production incidents, and collaborating with developers to improve deployment workflows. You're the person who ensures code gets from developer laptops to production safely and efficiently.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Required Skills: Beginner → Advanced</h3>
        <div class="skills-progression">
          <div class="skill-level"><div class="skill-level-header"><span class="skill-level-badge skill-level-beginner">Beginner</span><span class="skill-level-time">0–6 months</span></div><ul class="skill-level-list"><li>Linux fundamentals &amp; bash scripting</li><li>Git version control</li><li>Networking basics (TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP)</li><li>One programming language (Python/Go)</li><li>Docker basics</li><li>CI/CD concepts</li><li>Cloud platforms introduction</li></ul></div>
          <div class="skill-level"><div class="skill-level-header"><span class="skill-level-badge skill-level-intermediate">Intermediate</span><span class="skill-level-time">6–18 months</span></div><ul class="skill-level-list"><li>Kubernetes orchestration</li><li>Infrastructure as Code (Terraform)</li><li>CI/CD pipelines (Jenkins, GitHub Actions)</li><li>AWS/Azure/GCP services</li><li>Monitoring &amp; logging (Prometheus, ELK)</li><li>Configuration management (Ansible)</li><li>Security practices</li><li>Database administration basics</li></ul></div>
          <div class="skill-level"><div class="skill-level-header"><span class="skill-level-badge skill-level-advanced">Advanced</span><span class="skill-level-time">18+ months</span></div><ul class="skill-level-list"><li>Advanced Kubernetes (operators, Helm)</li><li>Service mesh (Istio)</li><li>Multi-cloud strategies</li><li>Performance tuning &amp; optimization</li><li>Disaster recovery planning</li><li>Cost optimization</li><li>SRE principles (SLIs, SLOs, SLAs)</li><li>Chaos engineering</li></ul></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Technologies &amp; Learning Order</h3>
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 1–3</span><h3>Linux &amp; Scripting</h3><p>Master Linux command line, bash scripting, file systems, process management. Set up your own Linux environment.</p></div></div>
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 4–6</span><h3>Networking &amp; Docker</h3><p>TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP fundamentals. Docker containers, images, volumes, networking. Containerize applications.</p></div></div>
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 7–10</span><h3>CI/CD &amp; Cloud</h3><p>Build CI/CD pipelines with GitHub Actions/Jenkins. Deploy to AWS/GCP. Learn cloud services (EC2, S3, RDS, Lambda).</p></div></div>
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 11–14</span><h3>Kubernetes &amp; IaC</h3><p>Kubernetes orchestration, Terraform for infrastructure as code. Manage production clusters. Implement auto-scaling.</p></div></div>
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 15–18</span><h3>Monitoring &amp; SRE</h3><p>Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack. Set up alerting, incident response, SLOs. Practice chaos engineering.</p></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span class="tag">Linux</span><span class="tag">Docker</span><span class="tag">Kubernetes</span><span class="tag">Terraform</span><span class="tag">AWS</span><span class="tag">GitHub Actions</span><span class="tag">Prometheus</span><span class="tag">Ansible</span><span class="tag">Python</span><span class="tag">Go</span>
        </div>
      </div>

