    <div class="roadmap-panel" role="tabpanel" id="panel-datascience" aria-labelledby="tab-datascience" hidden>

      <div class="roadmap-intro">
        <h3>Data Scientist / ML Engineer</h3>
        <p class="roadmap-intro-desc">Extract insights from data, build machine learning models, and turn raw information into business decisions. Combine statistics, programming, and domain expertise.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Role Overview &amp; Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>Data scientists analyze complex datasets to find patterns, build predictive models, and communicate insights to stakeholders. You clean and preprocess data, perform exploratory analysis, train and evaluate ML models, create visualizations, and deploy models to production. The role sits at the intersection of statistics, programming, and business understanding.</p>
        <p>Daily work includes writing Python/R code for analysis, querying databases for data extraction, building and iterating on ML models, creating dashboards and reports, presenting findings to non-technical stakeholders, and collaborating with engineering teams to productionize models.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Required Skills: Beginner → Advanced</h3>
        <div class="skills-progression">
          <div class="skill-level"><div class="skill-level-header"><span class="skill-level-badge skill-level-beginner">Beginner</span><span class="skill-level-time">0–6 months</span></div><ul class="skill-level-list"><li>Python programming fundamentals</li><li>Statistics basics (mean, median, distributions)</li><li>SQL for data querying</li><li>Data manipulation (Pandas, NumPy)</li><li>Basic data visualization (Matplotlib)</li><li>Jupyter Notebooks</li><li>Git version control</li></ul></div>
          <div class="skill-level"><div class="skill-level-header"><span class="skill-level-badge skill-level-intermediate">Intermediate</span><span class="skill-level-time">6–18 months</span></div><ul class="skill-level-list"><li>Machine learning (scikit-learn)</li><li>Feature engineering</li><li>Statistical testing &amp; inference</li><li>Advanced visualization (Seaborn, Plotly)</li><li>Data cleaning &amp; preprocessing</li><li>Linear algebra &amp; calculus</li><li>Model evaluation &amp; validation</li><li>Communication &amp; storytelling with data</li></ul></div>
          <div class="skill-level"><div class="skill-level-header"><span class="skill-level-badge skill-level-advanced">Advanced</span><span class="skill-level-time">18+ months</span></div><ul class="skill-level-list"><li>Deep learning (TensorFlow/PyTorch)</li><li>Natural Language Processing</li><li>Computer Vision</li><li>MLOps &amp; model deployment</li><li>Big data tools (Spark, Hadoop)</li><li>A/B testing &amp; experimentation</li><li>Cloud ML platforms (SageMaker, Vertex AI)</li><li>Research paper implementation</li></ul></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
        <h3 class="roadmap-block-title">Technologies &amp; Learning Order</h3>
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 1–3</span><h3>Python &amp; Statistics</h3><p>Master Python, learn statistics fundamentals, probability, distributions. Start using Jupyter Notebooks for analysis.</p></div></div>
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 4–6</span><h3>Data Manipulation &amp; SQL</h3><p>Pandas, NumPy mastery. SQL for data extraction. Data cleaning techniques. Exploratory data analysis workflows.</p></div></div>
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 7–10</span><h3>Machine Learning</h3><p>Scikit-learn: regression, classification, clustering. Model evaluation, cross-validation, hyperparameter tuning.</p></div></div>
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 11–14</span><h3>Deep Learning</h3><p>Neural networks with TensorFlow/PyTorch. CNNs for images, RNNs/Transformers for text. Transfer learning.</p></div></div>
          <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-marker" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="timeline-content"><span class="timeline-period">Months 15–18</span><h3>MLOps &amp; Deployment</h3><p>Model serving, monitoring, A/B testing. Docker for ML, cloud deployment, CI/CD for ML pipelines.</p></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span class="tag">Python</span><span class="tag">Pandas</span><span class="tag">NumPy</span><span class="tag">Scikit-learn</span><span class="tag">TensorFlow</span><span class="tag">PyTorch</span><span class="tag">SQL</span><span class="tag">Jupyter</span><span class="tag">Matplotlib</span><span class="tag">Spark</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="roadmap-block">
